Description:
Entry Level Buying At Its Very Best.
Forget the fixer upper and land banker; This one is the perfect entry level property for the genuine first home buyer, investor or long term developer. Set on an imposing allotment of approximately 710 square metres this beautifully presented 3 bedroom weatherboard home needs nothing more to make it complete other than a house full of furniture.
Updated with style the home is comprised of 3 spacious bedrooms, central living area with reverse cycle heating and cooling unit, adjoining dining area off the simple yet modern kitchen and updated bathroom featuring stylish tiling and quality fixtures.
Notable extras include new carpet and blinds and a fresh coat of paint right throughout, Impressive vinyl flooring in the kitchen and meals area and the entire exterior of the home has been given a once over to give the new buyer that new home feel when they move in.
Walking out to the massive rear yard is a sight to behold with a blank canvas waiting for the lucky purchaser to make their own and plenty of space for the kids to play in privacy or the budding developer will be licking their lips at the opportunity that presents (STCA). Theres ample car accommodation available with a long driveway leading down to a single car lock up garage with workshop space and for those that require public transport theres bus routes nearby that will take you to all that Geelong has to offer in only minutes. There are schools, 2 shopping centres, Splashdown and sporting facilities all within a short distance and once youre on the Bellarine Highway there is a world of fun available with wineries, Adventure Park and Daniels donuts in Portarlington all a nice Sunday drive away.
Dont delay as properties in this price range are as rare as hens teeth, make the time to inspect today and prepare to be impressed.

Description:
Great Location.
Here is great opportunity to get into the market or add to your property portfolio. This little hidden gem sits on a 590m2 (approx.) corner allotment and is secluded by the lush trees and shrubs that create a feeling of serenity. This 3 bedroom home comes complete with a study off the entrance and into the large open plan living area with large heater, functional kitchen with island bench and plenty of cupboards and storage space and a large dining room in the centre of the home. Bathroom with shower, bath and vanity and seperate w/c and good sized laundry. Outdoors is a good sized rear yard with a plenty of room the kids to play or the pets to roam, with a lock up garage and garden sheds. Located less than ten minutes to all amenities including Newcomb and Bellarine Village shopping centres, local schools and kindergartens, South Geelong train station and Geelong CBD.

Description:
Character & Charm in an Ideal Location
Situated only minutes' walk to the Geelong Botanical Gardens, East Geelong Shopping Precinct, Geelong CBD and the vibrant waterfront, this address is hard to surpass. This impressive home has been renovated, has an abundance of appeal and is ready for a family to occupy with a flexible floor plan which flows seamlessly from indoor to outdoor.
The beautiful main bedroom, which features an ensuite and walk in robe, is complemented by two further bedrooms and a study which are serviced by the impressive family bathroom. A separate formal lounge room with fireplace and a separate light-filled dining room.
The bright and well equipped kitchen features stone bench tops and top-of-the-range appliances. Adjacent to this space is the living room which opens through to the decked outdoor entertaining area and private, secure rear yard which is north facing.
This enchanting character home also includes heating and cooling, rooftop solar system, high ceilings, stunning leadlight glass and low maintenance gardens.
Positioned in one of East Geelong's premier streets and only minutes drive to local schools, Geelong Hospital, South Geelong railway station and less than 30 minutes drive to the ever popular Bellarine Peninsula. An inspection will not disappoint.

Description:
Character charm in highly sought location.
Looking for a character home in a highly desirable location? Look no further!
In a quiet, established street at the heart of East Geelong, this period home is in prime position. A short stroll around the corner takes you to the Garden Street cafe and shopping precinct, whilst schools, Eastern parklands and golf course, South Geelong train station, the Geelong CBD and waterfront are all at your doorstep.
With timber floors throughout the main activity areas, the home has a functional layout that comprises 3 carpeted bedrooms, open plan kitchen/ meals, generous living, central bathroom, separate laundry and toilet.
Period features include ornate roses, decorative cornice work, high skirts and timber sash windows, whilst gas ducted heating and a new oven, stove and dishwasher combine modern convenience with old world appeal.
Opening out to the north a paved undercover alfresco area is private and looks onto the grassed rear yard with enough space for pets and children to play in full view.
A double garage accessed from the side lane adds to the many benefits this beautiful property offers.
Don't miss your opportunity and contact Dion today on 0424 940 629 to learn more.

Description:
Refreshed for Easy Living
Take one step inside and feel at ease with the work, love and dedication that's been poured into this family friendly home. Freshly painted throughout, the centerpiece of the home is the revitalized kitchen with gorgeous wooden benchtops, a movable island bench and an abundance of storage space, but it also pleasantly features sparkling timber floor boards, three good sized bedrooms, wall heater, split system cooling to the master, a single car lock up garage with room for a workshop. Sitting on a block size of 560m2 (approx.), this charming and refreshed home has so much to offer and is ready to be yours!
With this superb location, you can easily walk to parks and sporting facilities, there are bus stops almost at your front door and if you need schools, kindergarten or day care, they're hidden around a few corners. This quiet locale has something for everyone.
When you head beyond the front garden, you'll walk inside to enjoy the WOW factor. The solid timber floors show strength throughout the home and flow throughout. The three zoned bedrooms are all of a good size, the master enjoys a split system unit, with built in wardrobe/cupboards to the other two and all serviced by a central family bathroom, which has also been updated and refreshed. The good sized, light filled living room features full length windows, wall gas heater, ceiling downlights and opens to a functional kitchen with outstanding timber benches and cupboards, dishwasher, gas stove & oven with a brand new rangehood. If you're an entertainer, the rear is the perfect spot to wine and dine with plenty of room for family occasions plus a great backyard for the kids or pets to roam around.
This home represents outstanding value in a hot Breakwater property market currently. Close to all amenities including East Geelong Primary School, Breakwater Pre-School Centre, Whittington War Memorial Kindergarten, First Steps Child Care Centre, Gordon TAFE East Geelong Campus, St Albans Sporting Reserve, Buckleys Entertainment Complex and only a few minutes drive to both Newcomb Shopping Centres, Geelong CBD and Waterfront. To enjoy all of the hard work that's been put into this extra special home, call today. This is sure to be snapped up fast, dont miss your chance!

Description:
NEAT AS A PIN IN GROWING NEWCOMB
This updated neat as a pin 3 bed, 1 bath brick home with DLUG with side access for all your parking needs, even caravan storage ticks all the boxes. Whether you are a downsizer where you can lock up and leave to chase the warmth, a young couple starting out or savvy investor with a potential rent of $370 pw approx. this property is one to inspect.
Set on a corner allotment of 530m2 approx with side gate access on Mercury Cres, this wonderful property comprises of spacious formal living room equipped with gas log fire and Mitsubishi reverse cycle split system for all year round comfort.
The central kitchen is tastefully updated and very spacious and offers ample cupboard space, brand new oven, 4 burner gas cook top, reverse cycle split system and an informal dining area easily accommodating up to 6. Down the hall you will find 3 good sized bedrooms all with block out blinds and one with BIR and ceiling fan.
The spacious bathroom has been updated and offers good size corner shower, separate bath and toilet, plus vanity storage and IXL heat lamps for those chilly mornings.
Outside you will find a small garden fernery, large paved courtyard with space for a caravan, trailer or two additional cars plus a large DLUG with side gate access.
This wonderfully updated home is ideally located less than 10 minutes walk to Eastern beach and approx 3km to Geelong CBD and less than 20 minutes to Bellarine Peninsula coast.
FEATURES
2 x reverse cycle split systems
Gas Heating
Updated bathroom and kitchen
Side access with caravan storage available
530 m2 corner block

Description:
Character and Class In The Heart of East Geelong.
Location, style, presentation and space; this one ticks all the boxes. Set on a private allotment of approximately 453 square metres and with rear lane access this magnificent example of Victorian elegance combined with modern style is the perfect family home for any astute buyer searching for a genuine family home in an unsurpassed location. Tastefully updated throughout, the home features a versatile floor plan made up of 4 light and inviting bedrooms, all with polished Baltic pine floorboards, double blinds and 12 foot ceilings, spacious central living area with ornate fireplace and the centrepiece of the home which has to be the outstanding open plan kitchen and meals area that leads out to the balcony and paved entertainment area through the cleverly designed bi-fold doors. As an added luxury the dining area windows can be also opened right up to further convey the feeling of space and fresh air. An abundance of extras include ducted heating throughout, practical and intelligently designed bathroom with classic neutral tones and high quality tiling and finish, stainless steel appliances and fixtures in the very chique kitchen and beautiful cottage gardens that complement the style of the home while the olive trees off the entertaining area overlooking the rear yard give off a very Mediterranean vibe! The double car lock up garage with remote control at the rear of the home is perfect for the mobile family and theres additional options for boat, caravan or trailer storage through the back gates. For those that dont drive theres also access to public transport practically right outside the front door. Above all else the location of this home sets it apart from the rest. Only minutes from Garden St. shops, Geelong C.B.D, St John of God and Geelong hospital, South Geelong train station and GMHBA stadium this is the ultimate lifestyle property and with the impressive infrastructure improvements happening in and around the Geelong area its no wonder why it will be in such high demand. Address: 21 Alcott Road St Albans Park VIC 3219
Description:
Modern Luxury with Lifestyle Convenience
With an immaculate street presence, this stunning custom built residence offers superior quality, functionality and modern contemporary living at its absolute finest.
When you head beyond the front garden, you'll walk inside to enjoy the WOW factor and feel a sense of welcome and warmth. This meticulously maintained home featuring quality modern timber laminate floors that show strength throughout the home, combined with soft quality carpets through this well thought out spacious home.
The clever floorplan allows for open yet dedicated living areas, which include an open plan kitchen, central family and dining area with the living zone serviced by split system heating & cooling unit and a second living room for that all important separate private space.
The spacious quality kitchen is the centrepiece of this wonderful home and features stone bench tops, brand new Kleenmaid dishwasher, 900mm electric oven, 5-burner gas stove top combination, instantaneous boiling hot water tap unit and an abundance of storage and bench space.
Three bright generous bedrooms and study/nursery includes the master suite, which boasts a walk-in robe, split system heating & cooling, ensuite with vanity, shower and toilet. The other two bedrooms are complete with built in wardrobes and are serviced by a central family bathroom with corner spa bath. All bedrooms have ceiling fans installed and there is Braemar ducted gas heating throughout the home as well. The large laundry area has also been thoughtfully designed and positioned with loads of storage for the larger family. Car accommodation consists of double remote garage with access to backyard. And for those buyers looking for that all important side access for trailer/boat/caravan, this is the one with a double carport complete with a high pitched gable roof adjacent to an additional double garage or workshop with 3 phase power. As well as room on the side leading through gates to a low maintenance large back yard. Perfect for tradies or leisure craft users.
Stepping out back you will be impressed with the brilliant undercover alfresco area, ideal for large family or social gatherings and year round entertaining. The adjacent rear yard is ideal for the kids or pets to roam around.
Other quality inclusions include: Security shutters on all windows; 6kw (24 panel) solar power system; Full service built-in bar to the main living zone; Security (4) camera system; Quality aluminium windows throughout; Fully insulated; LED downlights throughout; 1,700lt water tank; garden shedding and front and rear garden watering system.
All of this set on a very generous 786m2 approx. allotment in a quiet pocket of St Albans Park, you can easily walk to parks, there are bus stops nearby and if you need schools and sporting facilities, they're hidden around a few corners. This quality home has something for everyone. This is a lifestyle opportunity not to be missed, call today!
